        <abstract> 
<p>Encloses letters from H. G. Bronn, Asa Gray, and C. J. F. Bunbury, concerning the <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi>.</p> 
            <p>Will send review by Gray and a notice by Bronn.</p>
            <p>Says Bronn will superintend the German translation.</p> 
<p>Comments on lecture by Huxley [at Royal Institution, 10 Feb 1860, <hi rend="italic">Not. Proc. R. Inst. G. B.</hi> 3 (1858–62): 195–200]. Has remonstrated with him for saying sterility is "a universal and infallible criterion of species".</p> 
        </abstract>
